Vice President Kamala Harris delivered a speech via teleconference at the 96th convention of the National Bar Association. She expressed her pride in being a former member of the association and highlighted the importance of lawyers in fighting for justice and removing barriers for marginalized communities. Harris emphasized the significance of the right to vote and the ongoing fight to protect it. She mentioned the efforts of state legislatures to enact laws that make voting more difficult and called for the passage of the For the People Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act. Harris praised the National Bar Association for its history of shaping legal and civil rights and encouraged its members to continue their work in defending democracy and ensuring equal participation for all Americans.